    <bioghist >
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Marjorie Ann Scott was born in Bedford, Virginia, on December 1st, 1947. She would go on to
        graduate from Westhampton College of the University of Richmond, Duke University, and the
        Andover Newton Theological Seminary. In 1989, Marjorie would become an ordained minister of
        the United Church of Christ for the Church of the Covenant in Boston. Others places where
        she would work include the Boston City Mission Society, Elizabeth Stone House, Assistant
        Pastor at Grace Church Federated in East Boston, and as an Associate Pastor at the North
        Prospect Church in Medford. Marjorie would pass away at the age of 61 on January 28th,
        2009.</p>
    </bioghist>
